cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.SI. 

The paper deals with the store-and-forward routing problem, which is a networking problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves analysis of algorithms and complexity theory, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The use of conditional expectations and probabilistic constructions suggests that it could also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
